result.execSummary:
The defendant Robert G Elwing was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Robert G Elwing in court with attorney Kevin Brian Dunn.  Andrea L Fendry appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in Court for Plea/Sentencing. Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that Defendant knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently waived his rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Elements; received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain Defendant's plea.  Court found Defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
